b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe15044.htm)  [Next](sbe15046.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBWG/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 2 (SBE15)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 65\n\n### THIRD ANUV\xc3\x82KA.\n\nHe perceived that breath 1 is Brahman, for from breath these beings are born;\nby breath, when born, they live; into breath they enter at their death.\n\nHaving perceived this, he went again to his father Varu _n_ a, saying: 'Sir,\nteach me Brahman.' He said to him: 'Try to know Brahman by penance, for\npenance is (the means of knowing) Brahman.'\n\nHe performed penance. Having performed penance--\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[65:1](sbe15045.htm#fr_236) Or life; see B _ri_ h. \xc3\x82r. Up. IV, 1, 3.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 4](sbe15046.htm)\n\n"